The paper focuses on analyzing Twitter and YouTube activity in the context of the Syria conflict, which involves a complex network of actors and relationships. This suggests that the paper could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), which both deal with analyzing networks and patterns of behavior. Additionally, the paper could also fall under the sub-categories of Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), or Computation and Language (cs.CL), as it deals with the use of social media in a conflict situation and the challenges of analyzing online political activism.
